page_title: 'Using your data with Azure OpenAI Service'
page_description: Use this article to learn about using your data for better text generation in Azure OpenAI.
chunk_content: Data formats and file typesAzure OpenAI On Your Data supports the following file types:* `.txt`* `.md`* `.html`* `.docx`* `.pptx`* `.pdf`There's an upload limit, and there are some caveats about document structure and how it might affect the quality of responses from the model: * If you're converting data from an unsupported format into a supported format, optimize the quality of the model response by ensuring the conversion:    * Doesn't lead to significant data loss.    * Doesn't add unexpected noise to your data.  * If your files have special formatting, such as tables and columns, or bullet points, prepare your data with the data preparation script available on GitHub.* For documents and datasets with long text, you should use the available data preparation script. The script chunks data so that the model's responses are more accurate. This script also supports scanned PDF files and images.
